; PaideiaOS IPC Phase-1 Smoke Test: Ring Wraparound
; P3-011c: Test head/tail wraparound modulo SLOTS_PER_CHANNEL
; Design reference: design/ipc/phase1-api.md §2.1, slots.pdx

module IpcSmokeWraparound

; Test: Wraparound behavior of head and tail indices

; Constants
TEST_CHANNEL_CAPACITY = 256      ; Match SLOTS_PER_CHANNEL for full wraparound
TEST_SLOT_SIZE = 256
SLOTS_PER_CHANNEL = 256

; Expected outcomes:
; 1. ipc_create_channel(256, 256) succeeds
; 2. Enqueue 256 messages (saturate)
; 3. Dequeue 256 messages (drain)
; 4. Head and tail have wrapped (head % 256 and tail % 256 have cycled)
; 5. Enqueue 256 more messages — succeeds (tests wraparound, not overflow)
; 6. Dequeue all — succeeds and verifies content
; 7. Repeat several times to stress the modulo arithmetic

; STUB: Constants and test outline only
; Runtime: Deferred to paideia-as Phase 7+

end module
